[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring SSH server implementation**\n\nI'm thinking about how we can connect to an SSH server using private key authentication. Creating an in-memory SSH server could be a solution, but I need to consider adding a test dependency — possibly using Apache SSHD. I want to modify the build.gradle to include org.apache.sshd:sshd-core. Since older versions of JSch support ssh-rsa and ssh-dss, I need to ensure compatibility with modern clients and the key generation process for public keys. It's a bit tricky, but doable!\n\n**Considering key generation methods**\n\nI'm exploring whether I should use the JSch KeyPair class to generate and write the private key through its public API. It sounds like a straightforward option, but I want to inspect the KeyPair API to see how it works. Understanding its functionalities will help me determine if it meets my needs for SSH key handling effectively. Let's dive into the API details to clarify this approach!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_093d359055feef9b016a1102b5e57881a287c46038fe22d610\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEQK-Q80NgdeZq11UGxc72rQsFGUkswPmHtk2K9ulVkUwHS9-iERfmF5URYcxjfuiOq_XcQqaJ9aGE-yWGTCHps8Dbi7hYvQVZJLSkt0Ib0spuaY2ysA5IqEpjNBp1zQzvI8fFqo8aaLkb1JviXwT5Z5loiCSaIWpXyPGTk1hXz5xmB6VcdPaOO6LnfYv47s8NbT3mgZUhGXjPpfRA1ioo6s27lllV2tjEsRWJPsn4P-EzYjGhgxWORCUEtpKJx4FlmwlqdtecwWebzx1qeONlvCDpvIdI26MlwiTKD33UQfpFyQwJ2uv8Bedy4ydgUJoZ5t49lOxEEG6uMtQPqxJRVmR_QtP0-M67qDKNqRspHTVqNl0eXOsZzcOa6Nlsl5tonBKT-sq3277mJKD5DgeIUr8_Ky1myLXQx73XFijI3QjDQJ2wFWUiuosCy-CmVMSiYhstpMg5loXuntRDqo9A8gAEgw9vUF5zQYcvI87b08xAxERQQvLPJTdpjCuRBveiF9VS6GkSldx4yaMu58hndHwRJKovQ1vIFoI8ouWSYBX490IEhL8dFYjOKMs0O6AOsbuIIZJWGs1yeAxm1nlSJC-5w5FcZXri1lIxvCnWvbHnnXhvZJCqaLHxD4tLz5aAYMZFHAct05IFSviPdMCdN4kuC_eWl2GqRls4lVAhCf3KbBmtNzLyC9G9lohfClLzn4Ls-psJz8RBlbZmBs30l6fMrt4W_yKwFF8guyxEuN3RtEtr7wUNSbPyrmyHW7iYgGxf1RtsqnPc8KCF35Rg