[thinking] **Analyzing native test execution**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering whether we’ll run into issues with metadata for our custom classes during native tests. By default, tests should execute under the native image, but if we set the config for test classes and call Class.forName, native reflection needs metadata. The agent may help generate that, but can’t be modified. I wonder if adjusting the user-code-filter to include our test classes will fix the issue or create more confusion. I should focus on this!
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Considering metadata for test classes**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about the dynamic metadata for test classes, and it feels risky to include them in library metadata since that could create unnecessary complications. I realize using test classes for Native Image might not be the best idea. There’s a user-code-filter that includes only library classes, and adding test classes could lead to unwanted metadata generation. I wonder if the metadata really should reflect those test classes, considering the potential consequences. It’s a tricky situation!
[thinking] 
